x zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530829\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104paf1665702561950.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/paf1665702561950.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/paf1665702561950.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"paf1665702561950\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Structure Editor Functions that Change the Active Path\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Structure editor functions that change the field that has focus can change the active path, as can ^STORE and ^ACCEPT.\n </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paf1665702561950__li_d11939e1_d11940e1_d11941e1\">^FIRST, ^LAST, ^NEXT, or ^PREV used in combination with ^FIELD. For each pair, this includes both the function pair (for example, ^NEXT^FIELD) and combined function (for example, ^NEXT_FIELD). These functions act on the field node (that is, the field that is being left).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paf1665702561950__li_d11942e1_d11943e1_d11944e1\">^FIRST, ^LAST, ^NEXT, or ^PREV used in combination with ^OCCURRENCE or ^OCC_WINDOW. For each pair, this includes both the function pair (for example, ^NEXT^OCCURRENCE) and combined function (for example, ^NEXT_OCC). These functions act on the last field node (that is, the field that is being left) and the last entity node (that is, the occurrence that is being left).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paf1665702561950__li_d11945e1_d11946e1_d11947e1\">^CURSOR_DOWN, ^CURSOR_UP, ^CURSOR_FAST_UP, and ^CURSOR_FAST_DOWN, in character mode. These functions act on the last field node (that is, the field that is being left) and the last entity node (that is, the occurrence that is being left), if appropriate.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paf1665702561950__li_d11948e1_d11949e1_d11950e1\">^STORE and ^ACCEPT. These functions act on all the nodes on the active path (that is, the last field and all entity occurrences).\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cib1665702561871.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Active Path for Runtime Processing</a><p>The active path determines where processing is applied in a runtime component, and the order in which it occurs. It leads from the current occurrence of the outermost entity down to the current occurrence of the innermost entity.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530829\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530829\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Structure Editor Functions that Change the Active Path Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Structure Editor Functions that Change the Active Path Structure editor functions that change the field that has focus can change the active path, as can ^STORE and ^ACCEPT. ^FIRST, ^LAST, ^NEXT, or ^PREV used in combination with ^FIELD. For each pair, this includes both the function pair (for example, ^NEXT^FIELD) and combined function (for example, ^NEXT_FIELD). These functions act on the field node (that is, the field that is being left). ^FIRST, ^LAST, ^NEXT, or ^PREV used in combination with ^OCCURRENCE or ^OCC_WINDOW. For each pair, this includes both the function pair (for example, ^NEXT^OCCURRENCE) and combined function (for example, ^NEXT_OCC). These functions act on the last field node (that is, the field that is being left) and the last entity node (that is, the occurrence that is being left). ^CURSOR_DOWN, ^CURSOR_UP, ^CURSOR_FAST_UP, and ^CURSOR_FAST_DOWN, in character mode. These functions act on the last field node (that is, the field that is being left) and the last entity node (that is, the occurrence that is being left), if appropriate. ^STORE and ^ACCEPT. These functions act on all the nodes on the active path (that is, the last field and all entity occurrences). Related Links Active Path for Runtime Processing The active path determines where processing is applied in a runtime component, and the order in which it occurs. It leads from the current occurrence of the outermost entity down to the current occurrence of the innermost entity. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}